Ad Text:
About the role
Join a top ASX-listed organisation in a hands-on role delivering climate-related disclosures and building long-term ESG reporting capability. You’ll help implement AASB S2 climate disclosures, ensuring reliable, well-governed ESG data. Working across Finance and Sustainability, you’ll support financial impact modelling, climate analysis, and reporting processes, while engaging senior stakeholders and shaping the organisation’s climate reporting strategy.

Duties
• Implement AASB S2 disclosures through data collation, reconciliation, analysis, and evidence management
• Support financial impact modelling, scenario analysis, and preparation of reports for senior stakeholders
• Coordinate internal communications, track actions, and support controls testing and assurance processes
• Validate ESG data, integrate systems, and produce dashboards and visualisations
• Drive process improvements to strengthen governance and reporting quality
• Collaborate across teams to deliver accurate, timely, and compliant ESG reporting

Skills and Experience
• Bachelor of Commerce or Accounting
• CA Qualified or part-qualified
• 3+ years in finance, accounting, risk, or ESG roles
• Strong analytical skills and confidence with financial and sustainability data
• Experience in reconciliations, controls testing, documentation, and assurance
• Knowledge of AASB S2 
• Detail-oriented, proactive, and able to manage competing priorities in a fast-changing environment

About the Company
This leading ASX-listed property group is committed to sustainability, responsible growth, and creating better communities. It offers a collaborative, inclusive culture where diverse perspectives are valued and individuals are empowered to make an impact.

To Apply
To discuss this opportunity in more detail, please reach out to Tom Clarke at tclarke@sharpandcarter.com.au

SkyCity Adelaide is seeking Remediation Quality Analysts to join our Remediation team, with opportunities available in both a permanent full‑time position and an 18‑month contract role.

About the Opportunity

This role focuses on delivering high‑quality assurance across our remediation activities, this includes data quality, internal processes and AML/CTF processes, ensuring work meets policy, procedural, and regulatory expectations. You will analyse remediation outputs, identify errors and trends, validate data, and contribute to audit readiness while working closely with internal teams to strengthen controls and support continuous improvement.




About You

You bring experience in quality assurance or the capability to quickly develop it, supported by knowledge of financial crime compliance, AML/CTF risks, and ideally casino operations. You’re confident reviewing varied work types, preparing insights for senior stakeholders, validating data, and providing constructive feedback. Your ability to build strong relationships, support training, and contribute to process uplift positions you to enhance the organisation’s remediation quality and operational integrity.




What's in it for you?

Besides working with great people and getting firsthand experience of SkyCity's newest entertainment offerings, you will also be rewarded with a range of employee benefits including;

Free employee meals available at our employee restaurant
Subsidised car parking and public transport tickets.
Discounts available across SkyCity Adelaide venues.
Discount health insurance, free flu vaccinations, skin checks and other health checks.
Employee reward and recognition programs.
Fantastic career and professional development opportunities.
Access to Employee Assistance Program (EAP)

No recruitment agencies please.

At SkyCity, our career opportunities are as diverse as our workforce. We don't just embrace differences; we value and support them. Our hiring is centred on capability and performance, regardless of gender, gender identity, race, origin, age, educational background, disability, or religious beliefs. We're here to empower you to shine. Our willingness to adapt ensures you can chart your path with us! Join us at SkyCity and be extraordinary by being you.

Position Overview We are seeking an experienced Senior Data Quality Engineer with strong expertise in ETL processes, Snowflake data warehousing, Alteryx workflows, and Python scripting. The ideal candidate will be responsible for ensuring the accuracy, reliability, and consistency of data across various platforms and will work closely with data engineering and analytics teams to develop and maintain automated data quality frameworks. Key Responsibilities

Design, develop, and maintain automated data quality and validation frameworks to ensure the integrity of data pipelines.
Collaborate with data engineering teams to understand ETL processes and identify potential data quality issues.
Perform data profiling, cleansing, and validation using tools such as Alteryx and custom Python scripts.
Build and optimize data quality checks and tests in Snowflake environments.
Monitor data quality metrics and generate reports to highlight data issues and trends.
Work with stakeholders to define data quality rules and standards.
Troubleshoot and resolve data quality issues in a timely manner.
Document data quality processes, standards, and best practices.
Mentor junior team members and contribute to process improvements.

Salary: Love Health & Wellbeing so do we!
Ad Text:
Allow your analytics, communication and passion for creating outcomes lead the way to your success.
We have leading Parental Leave along with return-to-work perks for new parents - designed for both parents! 
Proudly partnered with The Smith Family supporting First Nations Youth Education 
About Iplex


At Iplex we are committed to a powerful vision – Providing Safe & Secure Water to the World Around Us. We do this by forging partnerships with our customers and communities to deliver safe, secure, and innovative water solutions that not only address the present needs but also lay a solid foundation for future generations. 


As Australia's leading manufacturer and supplier of pipeline systems, we take pride in our pivotal role within Australia’s water industry. We understand the significance of our work, and we are driven by the shared goal of creating a better future.  Join us today to lead a passionate team dedicated to shaping a brighter future and leaving a lasting impact on Australia's water landscape. 


What is Your New Role About? 


We have recently redesigned the role of Program Analyst based in Strathpine to ensure we get the outcomes we need. You will take complex, raw data from multiple internal and third-party sources and transform it into clear, compelling insights, executive packs and visually engaging decks that support informed decision making across a diverse group of leaders. Reporting to the Program Contracts and Performance Manager you will play an integral role in budgeting, forecasting, performance tracking and governance reporting, ensuring our Program remains on track across scheduling, cost, turnaround and build times. 


Working within a small, collaborative and supportive team, this role is ideal for someone who enjoys both analytical depth and human connection. You will partner closely with internal stakeholders and external providers, confidently drawing data together, challenging assumptions and communicating insights with clarity and influence. Exposure to governance, compliance and fast‑moving timeframes will be key, along with the ability to adapt, prioritise and stay calm under change. 


Ideal Skills & Experience 
Relevant qualifications in either Finance, Statistic, Data Analytics or related discipline 
You are the expert on all things digital Excel, Power Bi, Tableau, SAP, JDE or similar 
Proven experience creating high quality executive reports, data sets and presentations
Comfortable working with third party data sources to track outcomes and opportunities
Confident in working in fast changing environments with variable priorities 
Passionate about building trust, listening and influencing stakeholders 
Exposure to regulatory compliance frameworks would be highly regarded 
Why Join Our Team at Iplex 
Excellent Remuneration for the right candidate
Enjoy flexible work arrangements – 2 days from home
Rare opportunity to join a major program in a leading business
Leading parental leave policy – 26 weeks paid for primary caregiver
Amazing return-to-work options for parents coming back from parental leave  
We are endorsed by Reconciliation Australia for our Innovate RAP
Paid industry Membership to help grow your career ie NAWO
Proud partners of The Smith Family supporting youth education 
We are Proudly an equal opportunity employer, we welcome applications from people of all diverse backgrounds and identities, including Aboriginal & Torres Strait Islander Peoples, people with disability, culturally and linguistically diverse communities, LBGTQIA+ People and Veterans.
No Agency Support Required -Thank you

Our Company

Changing the world through digital experiences is what Adobe’s all about. We give everyone—from emerging artists to global brands—everything they need to design and deliver exceptional digital experiences! We’re passionate about empowering people to create beautiful and powerful images, videos, and apps, and transform how companies interact with customers across every screen. 

We’re on a mission to hire the very best and are committed to creating exceptional employee experiences where everyone is respected and has access to equal opportunity. We realize that new ideas can come from everywhere in the organization, and we know the next big idea could be yours!




The Opportunity

The Adobe Security Coordination Center is seeking an experienced Senior Cyber Defence Analyst to play a key role in investigating, analysing, and responding to complex cybersecurity incidents. Your expertise across Windows, Linux, server environments, and cloud technologies, coupled with strong analytical capabilities, will be crucial in swiftly identifying threats, managing incidents, and safeguarding Adobe's critical assets and business operations. If you're passionate about cybersecurity and want to help shape and elevate our defensive capabilities, we encourage you to join our global team!

What You Will Do

Conduct detailed cybersecurity investigations, leveraging critical thinking to identify indicators of compromise and coordinating effective incident containment and response.

Manage cases meticulously, documenting all investigative actions clearly to support accurate resolutions.

Engage in varied rotational activities within the Security Coordination Center, including incident response, cyber threat hunting, and detection engineering.

Lead case reviews, identify improvements in investigative processes, and provide mentorship to junior analysts.

Participate actively in tabletop exercises and incident simulations.

Continuously monitor emerging threats and maintain expertise in the evolving cybersecurity landscape.

Actively engage as an integral member of a global, 24/7 cyber defensive operations team, including weekend coverage as part of a rotation.

Develop, refine, and maintain detailed investigative process documentation.




What You Need To Succeed

Demonstrated experience in cybersecurity incident analysis and response, ideally within a high-performing Security Operations environment.

Hands-on experience with SIEM platforms (such as Splunk or similar technologies) and endpoint detection and response tools across multiple operating systems and environments (Windows, Linux, server, and cloud).

Strong familiarity with cybersecurity tools, threat intelligence, malware analysis, and network security fundamentals.

Exceptional analytical and problem-solving skills, enabling effective decision-making under pressure.

Ability to clearly communicate complex information to diverse stakeholders and technical teams.

Familiarity with compliance frameworks such as FedRAMP, ISO 27001, SOC2, HIPAA, FERPA, and PCI.

Excellent organizational skills, written and verbal communication abilities, and a collaborative approach to teamwork.

Proven capacity to multitask effectively in a dynamic, fast-paced environment.

Why Adobe?

Global company, local impact – part of a world-class 24/7 defence model

Salary meets global tech expectations — equity pushes it beyond.

Dedicated training and development budget to continuously expand your expertise

Wellbeing benefits including support for private health, fitness and lifestyle

Hybrid working – with a well-equipped office in Sydney’s CBD




You’ll be joining a newly formed, high-calibre team in Sydney, with existing Senior and Junior Analysts already in place.


At Adobe, you will be immersed in an exceptional work environment that is recognized throughout the world on Best Companies lists. You will also be surrounded by colleagues who are committed to helping each other grow through our unique Check-In approach where ongoing feedback flows freely. 

If you’re looking to make an impact, Adobe's the place for you. Discover what our employees are saying about their career experiences on the Adobe Life blog and explore the meaningful benefits we offer. 

Adobe is an equal opportunity employer. We welcome and encourage diversity in the workplace regardless of gender, race or color, ethnicity or national origin, age, disability, religion, sexual orientation, gender identity or expression, or veteran status. 

We will ensure that individuals with disabilities are provided reasonable accommodation to participate in the job application or interview process, to perform essential job functions, and to receive other benefits and privileges of employment. Please contact us to request accommodation




Adobe is proud to be an Equal Employment Opportunity employer. We do not discriminate based on gender, race or color, ethnicity or national origin, age, disability, religion, sexual orientation, gender identity or expression, veteran status, or any other applicable characteristics protected by law. Learn more.

Adobe aims to make Adobe.com accessible to any and all users. If you have a disability or special need that requires accommodation to navigate our website or complete the application process, email accommodations@adobe.com or call (408) 536-3015.

Company: Talent – Specialists in tech, transformation & beyond
Ad Text:
Our client is an iconic Australian organisation currently seeking a Senior Design Researcher to deliver integral research on a long term transformation project.

Your new role will see you joining the businesses Design and Research team to drive and manage research activities for internal partners in product, platform and enterprise. Ideally you will bring a wealth of experience driving research planning, roadmaps, and methodology in enterprise/ complex environments. Engaging with a range of internal stakeholders you will play a key role in utilising the appropriate research methodology to source data to inform decisions and reduce potential risks. This will be complete using moderated and unmoderated testing remote testing, a range of fidelity prototype testing, concept testing, contextual inquiry, survey design, competitive and comparative analysis, and other research methods across variety of devices.

Skills and Experience:

Strong experience as a Design Researcher within complex environments
Experience working with design research tools such as AirTable, Optimal Workshop, Askable, Miro and/or Figma
Good knowledge of accessibility
Comfortable working with ambiguity and adapting to change
Strong stakeholder engagement skills; comfortable engaging cross functional teams

Our client is offering an initial 6 month contract with the view to extension. Offices are based in Melbourne's inner suburbs with a requirement to be onsite 3 days per week.

For more information feel free to contact Ben Austin at ben.austin@talentinternational.com

Please note: This role will require both a CV and folio to be considered for submission

For over 30 years Talent has been redefining the contracting experience with industry leading support, exclusive contractor benefits & a world-class digital platform ENGAGE to access it all. Apply today to see how we can elevate your career

Senior Risk Analyst

Your opportunity

We have an exciting opportunity for a Senior Risk Analyst to support the Senior Manager– Enterprise Risk with assisting Scentre Group to systematically identify, assess, control, treat, review and report on risks impacting the Group’s ability to meet its business objectives including operating as a responsible and sustainable business.

Day-to-day you will be responsible:

To support the Enterprise Risk Team to assist Scentre Group to systematically identify, assess, control, treat, review and report on risks impacting the Group’s ability to meet its business objectives including operating as a responsible and sustainable business.

The Senior Business Analyst – Enterprise Risk is accountable for:

Supporting the development, preparation and enhancement of risk reporting to Senior Executives, the Board and Operational Teams including the maintenance of complete and accurate data in Bwise and tracking and recording of notable incidents and development and delivery of risk bulletins and updates.
Assist with the development, review, consultation and communication of risk management procedures, processes and tools, including associated change management and training programs.
Provide support to the Enterprise Risk Team in driving continuous improvement in key risk processes including Crisis Management Team Secretariat and Business Continuity Processes.
Provide support in the enhancement of the enterprise risk management and culture across Scentre Group through influencing, negotiation, learning and development programs, and communication platforms.
Provide support in the ASRS annual reporting process.
Assist with monitoring emerging risks. Industry trends and regulatory changes

This role is permanent, full-time

What sets you apart

Attention to detail to confirm risk deliverables are complete, accurate and of a high quality
Clear and concise communication skills (written and spoken) with people at all levels and from all different backgrounds
Enjoys problem solving, is process driven and analytical
Proven ability to multi-task and prioritise to achieve objectives of the Team
Proven ability to demonstrate strong execution and to deliver results to a deadline
Highly motivated and passionate to achieve the best possible outcome for the Team and the broader Group
Demonstrates initiative and curiosity and is comfortable challenging the status quo
A team player who is reliable, participative, and co-operative with other members of their team
Experience using Microsoft Office Suite and willingness to enhance data analytics, AI and reporting skills.

About us

Scentre Group owns 42 Westfield destinations across Australia and New Zealand. We create extraordinary places and experiences that connect and enrich communities.

We are focused on our customers and creating more reasons for more people to visit our Westfield destinations more often and for longer.

With approximately 75 professions within our business, our team has the expertise to design, construct, operate, manage and market our Westfield destinations and platforms.

We want to be the place where talent thrives. To support you thriving with us, we promise to respect, inspire and develop you, and that you will do work that matters.

Diversity, equity and inclusion underpins our culture, and our vision is that ‘Everyone Belongs’. We foster a workplace experience where everyone feels valued, supported and motivated to realise their full potential.

We aspire to create a workforce reflective of the communities in which we operate and encourage applications from everyone regardless of age, gender, ethnicity, cultural background, faith, disability, sexual orientation, gender identity or life stage.

We offer a range of unique benefits designed to support your wellbeing, career development and lifestyle, including five days paid Life Leave on top of your four weeks annual leave (pro-rated for part-time), 18 weeks gender neutral paid parental leave for primary carers, with no qualifying period and super paid for the duration of the leave period and free parking at your local Westfield destination.

Discover more about working with us.

Applications close: 27th February (unless filled prior).

Lead a talented team at Australian Retirement Trust to deliver powerful risk insights and analytics, driving smarter decisions and shaping the future of risk management. Use your expertise to transform complex data into clear, actionable intelligence that empowers senior leaders and makes a real impact.

Why join us?

You'll get 14% super as standard, to help your future come alive.
Unleash your potential and build a career to be proud of through excellent training and development opportunities.
Balance your work between in-person days at our purpose-built hubs and working from home.
In the office, enjoy end of trip facilities, a yoga and multi-faith room, parent and carer rooms, quiet rooms, BrewHub coffee facilities, and collaborative team spaces.

About the role

As the Manager, Risk Insights & Analytics at Australian Retirement Trust, you’ll play a pivotal role in transforming complex risk data into actionable intelligence that drives strategic decision-making across the organisation. You’ll lead a high-performing team, design innovative analytics frameworks, and deliver compelling visual reporting solutions for senior stakeholders. This is a fantastic opportunity to shape the future of risk reporting, work closely with executives, and make a real impact on organisational risk visibility. If you’re passionate about data, leadership, and continuous improvement, we’d love to hear from you!




Key aspects of the role include:

Leading the design and development of comprehensive risk reporting frameworks.
Delivering timely, accurate, and actionable insights to senior stakeholders and Board Committees.
Developing advanced analytics strategies and methodologies to support strategic decision-making.
Creating and maintaining executive dashboards and visual reporting tools.
Implementing predictive analytics and early warning indicators for proactive risk management.
Managing and mentoring a team of analytics and reporting specialists.
Collaborating with business areas and executives to understand and meet information needs.
Ensuring reporting solutions meet regulatory requirements and best practice standards.
Driving innovation in risk analytics, reporting capabilities, and data visualisation.
Supporting ad-hoc regulatory requests and maintaining compliance with relevant standards.

This role is a permanent opportunity based in Brisbane, Sydney, or Melbourne

About you

It goes without saying you'll be a great communicator with top notch interpersonal skills. We'll also expect you to pick up problems and come up with quick, creative ways to solve them. It's quite likely you tick some of the following boxes too:  

Proven expertise in advanced analytics techniques, including statistical modelling, predictive analytics, and data mining.
Strong experience designing and implementing comprehensive reporting solutions and executive dashboards.
Advanced proficiency with data analytics and business intelligence tools (such as Power BI or equivalent).
Deep understanding of risk management frameworks and translating them into measurable metrics and indicators.
Demonstrated ability to transform complex data into clear, actionable insights for diverse audiences.
Strong knowledge of database management, data warehousing, and ETL processes.
Experience leading and developing high-performing analytics or reporting teams.
Excellent stakeholder engagement skills, with the ability to gather requirements and deliver tailored solutions.
Solid understanding of regulatory reporting requirements and compliance standards.
Tertiary qualifications in Risk, Governance, Law, Business, or a related field (desirable).

About us

Our 2.4 million members trust us to take care of over $330 billion in retirement savings. And we help them take charge of their finances and face the future with confidence. Our inclusive culture means you’ll be valued and heard in a respectful workplace. We've created an environment where you can be yourself and do amazing work. It's that simple.

Apply online now

Everyone is welcome to apply. We value diverse thinking, cultures, perspectives, backgrounds, and abilities. Awaken your career at Australian Retirement Trust and apply now. Applications close 21st February 2025.

We don’t want to leave you with a monstrous wait. So, you’ll hear from us after the closing date to find out whether you’ve made it through to the next round or not. Being fair and up-front is important to us – and recruitment is no different.

Let’s create a more sociable future together

At Endeavour, we’re totally into what we do. With a portfolio that includes Dan Murphy’s, BWS, ALH Hotels, Pinnacle Drinks and more, we love to bring people together. Job Description
Flexible work arrangements / Hybrid pattern
A pivotal role within the work force planning function
Crunch data to optimise business performance and provide strategic insights

Sound good? Read on.

Location: Barangaroo, NSW or Alphington, VIC 
Division: Simpler for Stores – Retail Business Support 
Role Type: Full-Time, Hybrid working


About the Role
Are you a data-driven problem solver who loves translating complex numbers into real-world operational success? As our Workforce Planning and insights Specialist, you will be the engine behind the "Simpler for Stores" initiative. You’ll ensure that the business understand the complexities and opportunities that can drive productivity and profitability in our 350+ sites with 12,000+ team members, which will in turn ensure exceptional customer experiences.

You will be a strategic partner to our Operations teams, helping them navigate budgets, seasonal forecasting, dynamic trend changes and productivity improvements through actionable insights.

We’re moving toward a "simpler" store model, but the math behind it is anything but simple. We need someone who understands that managing labor isn't about the average - it's about managing the variance. We’re looking for a pro who uses standard deviation to build "risk-adjusted" models that account for the volatility in working hours across our footprint.

Why this role?

Scale: Influence the productivity of 12,000+ employees by narrowing the gap between "planned" vs. "actual" hours.
Tech-Forward: Use SQL, Tableau, and Python to move beyond flat forecasting into probabilistic labor simulations.
Visibility: You’ll be the subject matter expert coaching Brand Finance and Operationss leaders on how to interpret volatility and stabilize labor spend.


Key Responsibilities

Labour Modeling: support with the build of bottom-up labor budgets for 350+ sites using engineered labour standards.
Insightful Reporting: Create, present, and implement simplified, high-impact reporting to help Operations teams identify anomalies, trends, costs, and efficiency opportunities, as well as drive the link between workforce mix and strategy.
Forecasting: Project workforce requirements for major seasonal events and long-term business cycles.
Stakeholder Coaching: Partner with and coach Brand Finance and Operations teams on workforce planning best practices.
Productivity Optimization: Use data to identify performance gaps and support initiatives that make store operations "simpler."
Qualifications

Now let’s talk about you: 

Experience: 5 years in operational workforce planning (Retail or Hospitality experience is a huge plus).
Technical Skills: Advanced analytical and modeling skills. Proficiency in SQL and Tableau is essential; experience with Python or cloud platforms (Azure/AWS/GCP) is highly desired.
Education: A Bachelor’s Degree in Finance, Commerce, Engineering, or a related field.
Business Acumen: The ability to interpret Enterprise Agreements, awards, and wage reporting to drive productivity.
Communication: A knack for presenting data to cross-functional stakeholders in a way that is easy to understand and act upon.

 

The benefits are good too! 

We offer flexible working in every sense
An exclusive discount card for BWS, Dan Murphy’s, Woolworths, BIG W and other Endeavour Group brands, including our ALH pubs
Monthly meeting-free days 
Your health and wellbeing is your most important asset, and as one of our valued team members, it’s our first priority. You will have a range of free services to help you live well and support your physical, mental and financial wellbeing
Endeavour Group is full of opportunities - use our dedicated learning and development options to grow an idea, yourself, and your career. This is just the start, so dream big.

At Endeavour, we value being a workplace where everyone’s welcome - if you meet a number of the requirements (and not all), we encourage you to apply.

Additional Information

We are together creators

With a portfolio that includes Dan Murphy’s, BWS, ALH Hotels, Pinnacle Drinks and more, Endeavour Group is big on sociability. Together we create the moments that bring millions of people together. And together we have more fun, create more opportunities, and score a lot more goals. Job Description

At SEEK, we’re on a mission to help people live more fulfilling and productive working lives, and to help organisations succeed. Data is at the heart of how we do this — powering experimentation, personalisation, and intelligent product experiences used by millions across Asia-Pacific every day.

We’re looking for a Senior Analytics Engineer to join our Experimentation team — a pivotal role within SEEK’s AI & Analytics Data Products ecosystem. This role sits at the intersection of data engineering, experimentation methodology, and analytics, helping SEEK make evidence-based decisions at scale. SEEK uses a best-in-class experimentation platform, with this role contributes to building the data pipelines, models, and analytics layer that make experimentation trustworthy, scalable, and actionable.

The Role

As a Senior Analytics Engineer, you’ll build the trustworthy, scalable data assets that underpin SEEK’s experimentation and product analytics. You’ll transform raw data into well-modelled, documented, and tested datasets that data scientists and analysts can rely on to measure impact and drive insight.

You’ll work side-by-side with data scientists, platform engineers, and product teams to bring experiments to life — designing pipelines, solving data challenges, and shaping the analytics and data layer of SEEK’s experimentation platform.

This role blends technical depth with real business impact — perfect for someone who loves working with data that actively powers decisions, not just describes them.

Qualifications

What You’ll Do

Design, develop, and operate scalable SQL and dbt models for experimentation data (assignment, exposure, and outcomes).
Build reliability and observability into every dataset through validation frameworks, monitoring, and continuous improvement.
Partner with data scientists to enable trustworthy experiment analysis and design.
Shape SEEK’s experimentation platform, implementing scalable data models and metric frameworks.
Investigate and resolve data issues, identifying root causes and implementing lasting fixes.
Document, govern, and communicate — ensuring data assets are understood, accessible, and fit for purpose.
Lead by example, mentoring team members and contributing to analytics engineering craft and standards.
Collaborate across SEEK, engaging with central Data teams to align practices, tools, and best-in-class engineering standards.

About You
You’re passionate about high-quality data, strong engineering fundamentals, and the role analytics plays in shaping product strategy. You enjoy solving complex data problems and thrive in a collaborative, cross-functional environment.


You’ll Bring:
Advanced SQL skills and experience building production-grade data transformations.
Strong dbt experience (or equivalent) with focus on testing, reliability, and scale.
Experience working in cloud-based data environments (e.g. Databricks, Snowflake, or BigQuery).

Working knowledge of Python or PySpark for analysis or data validation.
Solid grasp of analytics engineering practices — version control, documentation, testing, and quality.
Statistical literacy to support experiment design and data validation.
Ability to translate analytical and experimentation needs into robust, well-modelled data assets.
Excellent communication skills and a collaborative mindset.
Confidence in leading technical design discussions, mentoring peers, and contributing to best practice evolution.

Bonus Points For:
Experience with experiment data, assignment and metrics pipelines.
Familiarity with Tealium, Segment, or other tracking systems.

Exposure to CI/CD for analytics (e.g. automated testing, dbt deployments).
Experience contributing to shared data infrastructure or governance initiatives.
Additional Information

The Team
You’ll report to SEEK’s Head of Experimentation and collaborate daily with:

Peers: Data Scientists, Data Engineers, Tracking Specialists, Analysts
Key Partners: AI Platform Services, Product Analytics, Product Management

Together, you’ll continue building SEEK’s evolving SEEK’s experimentation capabilities — enabling faster, more confident decision-making across the business.

Professional development sessions with industry leading guest speakers
Support of flexible working, including a mix of office and work from home days depending on your role
Annual Performance Bonus Plan

Challenger Limited is an ASX-listed investment management firm managing $123.9 billion in assets (as at 30 June 2025). Life with us is fast moving and always exciting. Together we’re driving to deliver our vision to provide our customers with financial security for a better retirement.

We achieve this goal by providing a work environment where people from diverse backgrounds, with a range of skills and experiences can contribute and succeed.

About the team and role 

The Investment Product team manages Challenger Life’s retail and institutional products, including fixed and lifetime annuities, life insurance contracts, reinsurance arrangements and investment products. 

The team is involved in the development of new products, the structuring of product features, and the development of pricing and risk models to ensure Challenger’s risk and return requirements are met. 

The team are looking to hire an Analyst to work alongside a team of specialised pricing actuaries and financial markets practitioners, providing financial modelling, pricing and transaction modelling support. 

In this role, the Analyst will be responsible for the ownership, development and operation of key models that are run weekly, as well as models used for transaction and projection-related tasks. These models are critical to team delivery, producing weekly product rates and supporting the economic analysis required for transaction structuring and approval. 

Key models include: 

Retail and institutional pricing models 

Reinsurance pricing models 

Annuity pricing models for ad-hoc quotations 

Transaction modelling support will vary by product and transaction and will span all aspects of product economics, including: 

Calculation of profitability, capital and risk metrics 

Scenario and stress testing 

Cleansing and analysis of data 

The Analyst will also be responsible for implementing Challenger’s model risk policy and overseeing the team’s compliance with these requirements, including model documentation and testing. 

About the candidate 

The ideal candidate will be highly numerate with strong financial modelling capabilities. They will have a strong analytical background, enjoy problem-solving, and demonstrate a high level of attention to detail. 

Clear communication skills and a collaborative working style are essential. 

Ideally, candidates will have financial modelling experience within the financial services sector and familiarity with insurance and banking products. 

Qualifications, experience and technical skills 

Strong academic track-record in quantitative disciplines such as Mathematics, Statistics, Physics, Engineering, Computer Science, Actuarial Studies, Finance/Economics etc.   

3–5 years’ experience in financial modelling or analytics 

Advanced Excel modelling skills are essential 

Familiarity with analytical tools such as Python and SQL would be advantageous 

Why Challenger? 
 
At Challenger, we’re small enough to be agile, but big enough to accelerate bold ideas. We support your growth and development, offering flexibility and a culture that values your unique contributions. 

Competitive discretionary bonus scheme  

18 weeks paid parental leave for all new parents

Extra superannuation contributions  

Employee share plan

Ad Text:
Our Purpose

Mastercard powers economies and empowers people in 200+ countries and territories worldwide. Together with our customers, we’re helping build a sustainable economy where everyone can prosper. We support a wide range of digital payments choices, making transactions secure, simple, smart and accessible. Title and Summary


Consultant, Advisors & Consulting Services, Strategy & Transformation
Consultant – Strategy & Transformation

Advisors & Consulting Services

Services within Mastercard is responsible for acquiring, engaging, and retaining customers by managing fraud and risk, enhancing cybersecurity, and improving the digital payments experience. We provide value-added services and leverage expertise, data-driven insights, and execution. Our Advisors & Consulting Services team combines traditional management consulting with Mastercard’s rich data assets, proprietary platforms, and technologies to provide clients with powerful strategic insights and recommendations. Our teams work with a diverse global customer base across industries, from banking and payments to retail and restaurants.

The Advisors & Consulting Services group has five specializations: Strategy & Transformation, Performance Analytics, Business Experimentation, Marketing, and Program Management. Our Strategy & Transformation consultants lead clients through impactful decision-making as they tackle strategic, tactical, operational, and transformational business challenges. They apply a broad set of problem-solving techniques to improve the client’s overall strategy, performance, and operations.

Positions for different specializations and levels are available in separate job postings. Please review our consulting specializations to learn more about all opportunities and apply for the position that is best suited to your background and experience: https://careers.mastercard.com/us/en/consulting-specializations-at-mastercard

Preferred qualifications

· Relevant industry expertise




Corporate Security Responsibility


All activities involving access to Mastercard assets, information, and networks comes with an inherent risk to the organization and, therefore, it is expected that every person working for, or on behalf of, Mastercard is responsible for information security and must:

Abide by Mastercard’s security policies and practices;

Ensure the confidentiality and integrity of the information being accessed;

Report any suspected information security violation or breach, and

Complete all periodic mandatory security trainings in accordance with Mastercard’s guidelines.

Qualifications:

Lean and/or Six Sigma (Green/Black Belt), Change Management, and Project/Program Management, preferred but not essential
A Business Degree or equivalent industry experience.
Experience with Business Process Management (BPM) tools;

Skills:

Ability to build collaborative relationships across a multinational organisation.
A straightforward, persuasive communicator who can simplify complex data.
A proven ability to motivate teams and drive a positive, safety-conscious culture.

Shopping discounts across hundreds of retailers
Generous parental leave entitlements
Travel discounts for flights, rental cars and accommodation

Ad Text:
Company description:



When you choose AusNet, you'll join genuine people working together, making Real. Progress

At AusNet, we're the link between renewable energy sources and local communities, playing a key role in the clean energy transition and providing essential energy to every Victorian family. AusNet's gas network is an essential service for homes and businesses in Western Victoria and will remain a critical part of the energy system for decades to come.

Help us lead the way, while enriching your career with real people who encourage you to bring your best and make real impact - for your career, our communities, and Australia's cleaner energy future.



Job description:



Purposeful work with genuinely good people. That's refreshing.

The future of gas is evolving. As owners of both electricity and gas networks in Victoria, we have a front row seat to how customer behaviour is changing and how the energy system will change, and the gas network will continue to play a critical role through this dynamic period. We need strategic thinkers to collaborate on maintaining a safe and reliable network, promoting price stability, and planning for our future role. As Strategy Lead, you'll help shape this future - bringing insight, creativity, and influence to one of the most significant transitions in Australia's energy landscape.

This role will deliver real outcomes, including but not limited to:

Developing a long-term strategic agenda for the gas network and pathway to implementation.

Undertaking rigorous research and analysis to assess risks and opportunities.
Driving execution of strategic initiatives and responding rapidly to emerging issues.
Preparing insights and recommendations for the Board and Executive Leadership Team.

You don't need to check every box; however, we are looking for a good combination of:

Demonstrated experience in strategy roles (consulting, corporate strategy, or similar).
Strong analytical and financial modelling skills, with advanced Excel and PowerPoint capability.
Excellent communication skills and ability to influence at executive level.
Energy sector experience is a plus, but not essential.

A real place to belong

We celebrate unique voices, refreshing perspectives and diversity in our team. Engage and connect through our social club, family day, wide range of events or by joining one of our Employee Network Groups.

We believe in more than just competitive pay. Here's what sets us apart:

Development: Exposure to AusNet's ELT, plus mentoring from a leader with top-tier consulting experience.
Flexibility: Hybrid work and flexible hours to help balance work and life.
Leave: Generous 14 weeks paid parental leave, with no minimum service.
Community Giving: A paid day to volunteer for a cause that matters to you.
Perks: Purchased leave, income protection insurance, novated leasing, corporate discounts, private health cover discounts and more.

As an industry in transformation, we're excited by the possibilities ahead.

So, if you're passionate about our purpose and committed to making real progress, bring your energy and join AusNet. Together, we can shape a new way forward.

About Our Client

Our client is a leading, government funded organisation which is going through a large digital transformation. As key part of this evolution is scaling their current data capability to support their reporting, analytics, and emerging AI capability.

Role Purpose

This role will play a hands-on and highly influential role in designing, building, and enhancing the organisation's cloud-based data platform.

You will walk into an established snowflake platform, one fit for current purpose, but one being assessed, evaluated and subsequently redesigned for future use. This position will be key to shaping how the platform evolves to be fit for purposes, working closely with the Head of Data and key business stakeholders. You will be involved in vendor section and then management to enable you to scale a team and get the new platform up and running over the next two years.

This isn't a data architect position, but a senior engineer or team leader looking to step into a managerial role whilst remaining hands on technically. You will have a lot of involvement in scope and solution design, taking the lead in scaling and redesigning the platform.

This role is central to improving data accessibility, delivering high-quality data assets, and enabling analytics and advanced data initiatives across the business.

Due to the nature of the data, this role is only open to Australian Citizens, or those with Permanent residency who are on the path to citizenship.

Key Responsibilities

Data Engineering & Design

- Design and deliver scalable data pipelines and data models using modern cloud technologies.

- Build and maintain the organisation's data engineering layer within Snowflake and Azure.

- Develop robust ELT/ETL patterns across batch, CDC, event-driven, and API-based integrations.

Data Platform Delivery

- Oversee platform reliability, monitoring, optimisation, and lifecycle management.

- Ensure data assets are secure, trusted, and well-governed.

Vendor & Partner Management

- Work closely with external vendors and MSPs to ensure high-quality engineering outcomes.

- Provide guidance, technical direction, and quality oversight across delivery partners.

Analytics Enablement

- Provide strong data foundations to support business intelligence, analytics, and emerging ML/GenAI initiatives.

- Translate stakeholder needs into fit-for-purpose technical designs.

Capability Building

- Establish and document best-practice engineering standards and patterns.

- Play a key role in shaping and contributing to a future data engineering team.

Essential Knowledge, Skills, and Experience

- Hands-on technical experience with Snowflake, databricks, dbt, Python, and Tableau.

- Strong ability to design scalable data models and pipelines (without needing to be an enterprise architect).

- Practical knowledge of Azure data services and cloud-native engineering patterns.

- Experience working with ingestion methods including APIs, CDC, batch, and event-driven architectures.

- Familiarity with BI tools and semantic layers (Tableau or Power BI).

- Understanding of governance and metadata tools such as Microsoft Purview.

- Demonstrated vendor management and external delivery oversight experience.

- Excellent communication skills with the ability to simplify complex concepts.

- Experience working within agile, cloud-based engineering environments.

- Relevant tertiary qualifications or equivalent experience.

What's on Offer

- A highly influential role as a key hire within the expanding data function.

- Ownership of a modern, cloud-native data platform and engineering stack.

- Opportunity to contribute to the design and formation of a future data engineering team.

- Exposure to advanced analytics, ML, and AI initiatives.

- Flexible working arrangements (Sydney based).

- $170,000 - $190,000 inc super plus benefits

The Opportunity

As a Strategy Manager, you will join Ramsay Health Care’s expanding Group Health & Strategy Team and play an integral role in delivering the Ramsay 2030 Strategy. Working closely with the Group Strategy Team, the Group Chief Health & Strategy Officer, and senior leaders across Australia and the broader Ramsay Group, you will help shape and implement strategic initiatives that support Ramsay’s next phase of growth. The role offers broad exposure across strategy, operational performance, and high-impact projects, with opportunities to contribute both locally and across Ramsay’s international operations.

What You Will Bring

You bring strong analytical and commercial capability, with the ability to work through ambiguity and complexity in fast-paced environments. You take a hypothesis-driven approach, leveraging data and insight to develop clear, well-structured strategic recommendations that support confident decision-making.

Key Accountabilities:

Lead and deliver strategic workstreams aligned to the Ramsay 2030 Strategy.
Support effective decision-making by driving operational rhythm, cadence, and cross-functional alignment.
Identify, scope, and deliver high-impact strategic projects, including M&A, partnerships, and transformation initiatives.
Develop clear, data-driven insights through analysis, modelling, and storytelling for senior leaders and executives.
Prepare business cases, cost-benefit models, KPIs, and performance reporting to support strategic priorities.
Partner with leaders across Strategy, Operations, and Corporate teams to embed strategy into day-to-day business execution.

Skills & Education

3–5 years’ experience in strategy, management consulting, corporate development, healthcare operations, investment banking, or a similar analytical environment.
Strong problem-solving and quantitative skills, with the ability to work confidently in ambiguous or fast-changing contexts.
Excellent written and verbal communication skills, including the ability to prepare high-quality executive presentations.
Advanced capability in PowerPoint and Excel, with experience in business case development, KPI tracking, and market analysis.
Tertiary qualification in Data Science, Finance, Accounting, Engineering, Economics, Management, or a related discipline (preferred).
Healthcare and/or transformation experience (desirable).
Experience with analytics and data tools such as Google Cloud Platform (BigQuery), TM1, SQL, VBA, Python, or R (desirable).

Benefits

An attractive remuneration package, supported by a comprehensive range of benefits that recognise your contribution and promote your wellbeing.
Opportunities for leadership and professional development, with clear pathways for career growth across Australia’s largest private healthcare provider.
Access to an exclusive rewards program offering premium discounts and privileges with leading national and global brands.
The chance to join a purpose-driven organisation at a pivotal time, where you can contribute to meaningful transformation and help shape the future of high-quality healthcare across the Ramsay network.

About Ramsay Health Care

Founded in Australia in 1964, Ramsay Health Care is the nation’s largest private hospital operator and a global healthcare leader. In Australia, Ramsay operates 76 hospitals and 12 surgical centres, caring for more than 1.1 million patients each year across acute care, complex surgery, mental health, and rehabilitation, alongside public hospitals, clinics, telehealth-supported psychology services, and community pharmacies. With around 35,000 employees and partnerships with more than 9,000 doctors, Ramsay is recognised for strong clinical governance, high-acuity care, and leadership in clinical trials. About Us

With a focus on innovation and delivering better customer outcomes, there has never been a better time to work in the Tasmanian energy sector with Aurora Energy. Be a part of Tasmania’s energy future and make a strong contribution to the ongoing success of our business. 

We work hard to create a workplace that is welcoming and flexible, while balancing the needs of our people, the business and our customers. Our ‘Better Fit’ Program offers hybrid working after a training and/or probationary period to support work-life balance. 

Aurora Energy will invest in you with training and education, celebrate your successes through recognition and reward, and provide a range of employee benefits including an electricity discount, generous leave benefits, and support for your health and wellbeing.  

We believe that every employee has a role to play in contributing to a positive and supportive workplace culture. Our Aurora Way values have been created by our people, for our people. As an employee, you’ll use these values every day to guide your behaviours and actions. Together we’ll continue to make Aurora Energy a great place to work.  

This role sits within our Digital Transformation and Operations Business Unit. They are at the forefront of developing and rolling out new technologies, partnering with the business to solve complex problems, keeping Aurora Energy’s data and systems secure, and much more.   

They collaborate with stakeholders across Aurora Energy to understand problems and identify the best way forward. They take a team-based, people-centric approach. In their words: “There are lots of exciting things to do to support Aurora Energy’s digital transformation, and this breadth is what keeps it interesting.”  

Digital Transformation and Operations is made up of three parts. The Senior Data Engineer sits within Digital Operations.

Digital Operations is made up of an Infrastructure Team, Tech Contracts, Cyber Security, and Service Delivery. Collectively they make sure that all the technology we use in the business, including our systems and reports, is functional and well maintained. They also provide hands-on support for our in-house projects. They are known for being early adopters and champions of new technologies including GenAI.    

About the Role

As our Senior Data Engineer, you’ll lead a talented team and play a hands‑on role in building data solutions that support smarter decisions, better customer experiences and Aurora Energy’s digital future.

You’ll work closely with teams across the business to design, deliver and continuously improve our data and analytics platforms – while championing innovation, quality and good data governance.

In this role, you’ll:

Lead and mentor a team of data engineers.
Design and deliver scalable data and analytics solutions aligned to business goals.
Act as the go‑to expert for complex data engineering challenges.
Drive continuous improvement across our data platforms, tools and ways of working.
Champion agile and DevOps practices, collaboration and learning.
Partner with stakeholders, delivery teams and vendors to get outcomes across the line.

About You

You’re a technically strong leader who enjoys solving problems and helping others succeed. You’re comfortable balancing hands‑on delivery with strategy, and you’re curious about how data can create real value.

You’ll bring:

A degree in computer science or a related field, or equivalent experience.
Strong experience in data engineering, analytics and business intelligence, including cloud platforms.
Experience leading or coaching engineers or analysts.
Solid problem‑solving and solution‑design skills.
Confidence working with stakeholders in a fast‑moving environment.
Experience working in agile teams and a passion for continuous improvement.

Experience with Snowflake, cloud‑based data transformation tools or data governance frameworks is a plus. At least two years’ experience in a similar role is desirable.  

What’s on Offer

With a focus on innovation and delivering better customer outcomes, there has never been a better time to work in the Tasmanian energy sector with Aurora Energy. Be a part of Tasmanians’ energy future and make a strong contribution to the ongoing success of our business.

We work hard to create a workplace that is welcoming and flexible, while balancing the needs of our people, the business and our customers.

Our ‘Better Fit’ Program offers hybrid working after a training and/or probationary period. Our offices feature collaborative spaces, quiet pods, sit/stand desks, and meetings rooms of all sizes—all fully integrated with the latest collaborative working technologies and amenities.

How to Apply

If you have what it takes, please click ‘I’m interested’ or 'apply', ensuring you attach a cover letter outlining how your skills and experience are aligned with this role, as well as an up-to-date resume. Applications without a cover letter will not be considered.

You will be required to satisfy a National Criminal History Police Check. 

Applications close 9am Wednesday, 25 February 2026.

Job Title: Senior Business Analyst – Private Health Insurance (PHI)
Ad Text:
Role Overview

We are seeking a Senior Business Analyst with strong Australian Private Health Insurance (PHI) experience, particularly across memberships, products, premiums, and claims. This role supports business and technology initiatives within a health fund environment and requires a practical understanding of how PHI operations translate into system behaviour and data outcomes.

The successful candidate will be comfortable working across core PHI processes and supporting integrations with Medicare, HICAPS, and ECLIPSE, while collaborating closely with business SMEs and delivery teams.


Key Responsibilities
• Lead business analysis activities across PHI initiatives impacting membership management, product configuration, premium billing, and claims processing
• Work with business stakeholders to capture and document requirements related to:
• Member lifecycle events (joins, transfers, suspensions, terminations)
• Product and cover structures (Hospital, Extras, combined covers)
• Premium calculation, payment frequency, arrears, and advance payments
• Claims submission, assessment, and benefit calculation
• Analyse and document as-is and to-be processes, business rules, and system interactions
• Support initiatives involving external PHI interfaces, including:
• HICAPS (electronic and POS claiming)
• ECLIPSE (hospital and medical claiming)
• Medicare coordination and related interactions
• Translate business requirements into clear functional specifications and user stories
• Collaborate with solution designers, developers, and testers to ensure requirements are correctly implemented
• Support SIT and UAT by defining PHI-relevant test scenarios and validating outcomes against expected business rules
• Assist with implementation activities, change impacts, and post-release support

Mandatory Skills & Experience:


• Proven experience as a Senior Business Analyst within the Australian PHI domain
• Strong understanding of core PHI operations, including:
• Membership and policy administration
• Product and benefit structures
• Premiums, payments, and billing cycles
• Claims processing and benefit calculation
• Experience supporting or analysing PHI integrations such as HICAPS, ECLIPSE, and Medicare
• Ability to interpret fund rules and translate them into system and data requirements
• Strong documentation skills (business requirements, functional specs, process flows, user stories)
• Experience working in Agile, Waterfall, or hybrid delivery environments
• Strong stakeholder engagement and communication skills


Desirable Experience
• Experience working with PHI core systems.
• Exposure to PHI reporting, data, or reconciliation processes
• Experience supporting cutover, deployment, or go-live activities
• Familiarity with common BA tooling (JIRA, Confluence, Visio, etc.)


Key Attributes
• Solid understanding of PHI business processes and terminology
• Analytical and detail-oriented
• Comfortable working in regulated environments
• Collaborative and delivery-focused

Job Title: Senior Project Manager – Technology & Digital Transformation
Ad Text:
Senior Project Manager – Technology & Digital Transformation | Strategy Assist | Sydney-based only

Sydney, NSW · Hybrid · Full-time or Contract Opportunity

About Us
Strategy Assist is a boutique consulting firm that helps organisations deliver meaningful transformation across ERP, HCM, payroll, CRM, and digital platforms. We partner with businesses from mid-size to enterprise, empowering them to unlock growth through technology and innovation.

As we continue to expand our focus on digital transformation, AI, and automation, we're seeking a hands on Senior Project Manager to lead complex, enterprise grade technology projects across multiple industries, including professional services, healthcare, aged care, not-for-profit, and corporate sectors.

About the Role
This is more than a delivery role, it's a leadership opportunity for someone who thrives on driving outcomes, managing multiple high impact projects simultaneously, and working closely with clients to deliver tangible results. You'll take full ownership of project delivery across business applications, data transformation, AI automation, and digital integration, balancing strategic oversight with hands on execution.

You'll engage with senior stakeholders to ensure alignment between business goals and technology outcomes, while also identifying opportunities to expand services and strengthen client relationships.

Key Responsibilities

Lead multiple concurrent transformation programs with end-to-end accountability from inception to transition to BAU.

Oversee project governance, resource planning, budgeting, and risk/issue management across business and technology domains.

Develop and maintain trusted client partnerships through proactive communication and solution-oriented engagement.

Identify opportunities for value creation and new project initiatives with existing and prospective clients.

Drive structured project delivery frameworks that ensure consistency, efficiency, and quality.

Partner with clients to shape technology roadmaps across ERP, CRM, payroll, workforce, and automation solutions.

Mentor and develop project teams, promoting collaboration, accountability, and continuous improvement.

Ensure process and data interoperability across systems and business functions.

About You
You are a dynamic, business-minded leader who thrives in fast-paced, multi-project environments. You bring strong delivery discipline, commercial acumen, and a genuine passion for building relationships that drive business transformation.

Essential Requirements

Minimum 7+ years' experience managing large-scale digital or enterprise transformation projects.

Demonstrated experience managing transformation projects with budgets of $500K or above.

Proven ability to manage multiple projects simultaneously across diverse clients and sectors.

Strong record of stakeholder engagement, influencing at senior levels, and driving client outcomes.

Deep expertise across ERP, HCM, CRM, or related business applications.

Specific experience with Workday, Microsoft Dynamics, SAP, or any other major ERP, HCM, or CRM platform.

Advanced skills in governance, budgeting, risk/issue management, and reporting.

Proficiency with Microsoft Project, PowerPoint, Excel, and the Microsoft Office Suite.

Excellent written and verbal communication, including formal reporting and executive presentations.

Bachelor's degree in Business, IT, or a related discipline (or equivalent experience).

Hold a recognised project management certification such as PMP, PRINCE2, or equivalent.

Desirable Skills

Experience applying organisational change management methodologies (e.g., Prosci/ADKAR).

Familiarity with AI, automation, or data transformation initiatives.

Strong mentoring and people leadership experience.

Why Join Strategy Assist

Lead strategic transformation projects across multiple industries.

Collaborate with a senior team shaping the future of digital and AI-enabled consulting.

Work in a flexible, hybrid environment that values initiative and ownership.

Join an agile consultancy where your ideas and leadership directly influence success.

Eligibility
Only candidates based in Sydney with Australian Permanent Residency or Citizenship will be considered.

How to Apply
If you're ready to deliver impact across multiple projects and industries while building strong client relationships, send your résumé and cover letter to recruitment@strategyassist.com.au.

Please note: due to the volume of candidates, only shortlisted candidates will be contacted.

Join Strategy Assist and help redefine what's possible in digital transformation.

Alinta Energy is one of Australia’s biggest energy retailers, generators and developers with over 1.1 million customers. Australia’s energy system is undergoing the biggest transformation in its history and we’re right there with it. We’re investing in and developing large-scale renewables and storage projects as part of our ongoing effort to provide our customers with reliable, affordable and sustainable energy.

We understand that flexibility matters when considering your next role. Let us know your requirements, and we’ll carefully consider how we might accommodate them.

Ready to make a real impact?

Step into a key role within Alinta Energy’s Group FP&A function, where you’ll help shape group level financial insight and executive decision making. Reporting to the FP&A Manager, this role operates at a group wide level, consolidating financial performance, supporting forecasting and budgeting, and producing executive ready reporting. The position is offered as a maximum term contract for 18 months (parental leave cover) and plays an important role in maintaining continuity, accuracy, and confidence in financial reporting within a complex and fast paced environment. This is a highly visible role that combines strong financial governance, analytical depth, and clear financial storytelling.

Why you’ll love working here

At Alinta Energy, we’re taking real action to deliver reliable and sustainable energy for Australia — and that practical approach runs through everything we do. You’ll get clear direction, genuine flexibility, and the support you need to grow, all while working on projects that make a lasting difference. We’re big enough to create impact, but small enough that your ideas and effort will always be seen.

There are plenty of other great benefits of working for Alinta Energy, including flexible working, energy discounts, an Employee Assistance Program (EAP), a paid volunteer day each year, fully stocked kitchens, and lots more.

What you'll do

Deliver group level performance reporting (month-end, rolling forecast, board/executive packs) with clear variance analysis, risks, opportunities, and strong cash flow insights.
Support budgeting and forecasting timetables, partnering with finance teams and business partners to build accurate, forward-looking views.
Enhance financial models and Power BI dashboards, driving automation and consistent reporting in partnership with systems teams.
Respond to ad hoc analysis and executive queries, including owners and government.
Identify and lead process improvements across reporting and analytics to reduce manual effort and lift quality and speed.

Your experience

Proven experience as a Senior Analyst (FP&A/financial analysis) in a large or complex environment, producing executive-level insights.
Strong accounting foundation with a tertiary finance/accounting degree and CA/CPA (or equivalent).
Recent hands on with Oracle EPM (FCCS/PBCS), advanced Excel, and Power BI.
Exceptional written and verbal communication; able to translate complex data into clear narratives for senior stakeholders.
Proactive, analytical, and resilient, with the confidence to challenge assumptions, influence stakeholders, and meet hard deadlines.

Please note this role requires full working rights within Australia.

Like what you’re seeing?

If you like the sound of this, and you’ve got experience in a similar role, we’d love to talk to you. Come and discover better together with Alinta Energy.

We are a 2026 Circle Back Initiative Employer – we commit to respond to every applicant.

If your application progresses, we will need to complete background and pre-employment checks, such as immigration checks, reference checks, criminal background checks, qualification checks, and additional checks for roles related to finance.

Our Diversity Commitment

Alinta Energy offers a truly diverse, safe and supportive work environment. As an equal opportunity employer, Alinta Energy encourages applications from any qualified person, including First Nations Australians, members of the LGBTQIA+ community, people of all ages and people living with a disability. We are also proud to be a WORK180 Endorsed Employer and we are committed to advancing women’s careers.

We look forward to hearing from you.
